Turkey Considers Cross-Border Anti-Terror Operations, Sabah Says

-- B y   E m r e   P e k e r
-- 
2011-07-24T09:22:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/turkey-considers-cross-border-anti-terror-operations-sabah-says.html
Turkey ’s government is considering
enabling the police department’s special-operations unit to
carry out cross-border operations, Sabah reported, without
saying where it got the information.  Prime Minister  Recep Tayyip Erdogan  wants to broaden the
unit’s authority to match the military, which already has the
power to operate in neighboring countries, Istanbul-based Sabah
 said .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emre Peker in Ankara at 
 epeker2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Louis Meixler in  Jerusalem  at 
 lmeixler@bloomberg.net . 